HelpText.Helptext: Enter details for the opportunity. You can also modify the default filters for Role, Industry and Solution type
Select the qualification categories which you want to use to filter results
Select the sales stage which you want to use to filter results
You will be presented with a series of yes/no questions. Check each question for which the answer is 'yes'.
Select the method you want to use to publish the data.
Select the checklist items that have been completed
Select the customer questions you want to use
A list of tips for this stage of the sale will be displayed
Review self-coaching questions for this stage of the sales process, keep a track of activities you decide you need to undertake
Enter notes for the opportunity - you will be able to review them later
Select an opportunity to work with or create a new opportunity

SalesStages.StageDescription: Where we build insight in the form of competitive forces, the prospcts value chain, their marketing strategy, the tactics they are executing, the expternal forces that influence their decision making, the people, the organizational structure and culture
Where we first engage with the prospect - we disuss their business challenges and objectives, identify opportunities and discuss/agree a plan of action
The discovery stage is where we identify KPI's, business issues, related problems, business and personal motivations
Where we create an initial value proposition, which should include and estimated ROI (eROI)
Where we promote our value proposition, lay traps for competitors, continue to build support and neutralize ditractors
The formal business case development. Where the variables and valueare used to construct a formal business csase comprsing ROI, NPV, DCF, IRR etc. We should also conduct risk and sensitivity analysis
Where we plan a negotiation strategy, build our team, engage with the prospect and look to build a win-win agreement. The stage culminates in an executed agreement
Where we focus on delivering the value as described in the business plan. This is the stage the customer cares most about
Where we look to brickwall our account, expand the scope of our engagement and work to increase our importance in the eyes of our customer
